The Telegraph - Calcutta : Bengal
 Saturday, December 20, 2003 				 Door-to-door to collect phone dues
 OUR CORRESPONDENT																								Behrampore, Dec. 19: BSNL officials will knock on the doors of phone bill defaulters in Murshidabad for a month to collect dues worth Rs 6 crore. 																								We have offered a special discount to the defaulters till December 31, said Asim Sinha, the BSNL deputy general manager here. We have realised about Rs 2 crore but still have Rs 6 crore outstanding and so we will go to the subscribers, added Sinha. After that, we will move court. 																								Over the past five years, telephone connections to about 6,000 subscribers who had not paid their bills were snapped. Rebel remand																								Top Peoples War leader Asit Sarkar was today remanded in 14 days jail custody by the subdivisional judicial magistrate in Midnapore. Sarkar was arrested early this month.
